OL,3,CMum fears 'terrifying' energy cost of
OL,4,Ckeeping disabled son alive
OL,6,FA mother who cares for her severely
OL,7,Fdisabled son says she fears losing
OL,8,Ftheir home when the cost of energy
OL,9,Frises next month.
OL,11,FSamantha Tolmie's 20-year-old son
OL,12,FLewis has an extremely rare form of
OL,13,Fthe incurable degenerative condition
OL,14,FBatten disease.
OL,16,FComplications related to his condition
OL,17,Fmean he needs a range of energy-
OL,18,Fintensive equipment, including a
OL,19,Fventilator, to keep him alive at home.
