OL,3,CMum fears 'terrifying' energy cost of
OL,4,Ckeeping disabled son alive
OL,6,FThe cost of operating the machinery is
OL,7,Fset to soar when the Energy Price Cap,
OL,8,Fwhich controls what most households
OL,9,Fpay for energy, rises by 10% next
OL,10,Fmonth.
OL,12,FMs Tolmie said: "When the price
OL,13,Fincrease happened last winter, my
OL,14,Fdirect debit ended up being around
OL,15,F#500 a month and I was so afraid to
OL,16,Fspend any money at all, I went without
OL,17,Ffood sometimes. When it went down in
OL,18,Fthe spring it was such a relief.
