OL,3,CMum fears 'terrifying' energy cost of
OL,4,Ckeeping disabled son alive
OL,6,F"I'm just so afraid it could create a
OL,7,Fsituation where I can't keep him safe."
OL,9,FAnna Bird, chief executive of charity
OL,10,FContact, which supports families with
OL,11,Fdisabled children, said energy costs
OL,12,Fwere one of the main issues for people
OL,13,Fwho rely on the charity.
OL,15,FShe added: "In this time when prices
OL,16,Fare sky high a social tariff could
OL,17,Fmake a huge difference to families and
OL,18,Fbe the difference between getting by
OL,19,Fthis winter or really struggling to
OL,20,Fpay rent, heat homes and put food on
OL,21,Fthe table."
